{"id":5193,"date":"2024-01-28T06:34:36","date_gmt":"2020-01-28T01:04:36","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=5193"},"modified":"2022-12-22T22:39:18","modified_gmt":"2022-12-22T17:09:18","slug":"kitchenette-design-ideas","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchenette-design-ideas\/","title":{"rendered":"All You Need to Know About Kitchenettes"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>Learn all there is to know about kitchenette design ideas before installing or renovating yours.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Kitchenettes are the small hatchbacks of the kitchen world. Small and compact, they pack in most functions of a regular sized kitchen but just scaled down. A kitchenette may have a few or all the following: a sink, a fridge, a cooktop and an oven. It depends on the functional requirements the kitchenette is supposed to serve and the space available. You may want a tiny kitchenette in your basement \u2013 only a fridge and oven, for example, may meet your requirements. Others may have a studio apartment in which case the kitchenette needs to be fitted out with all the mod-cons. Our guide on the essential facts of kitchenettes will help you get the most of your space regardless.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Making The Most Of Cabinets For Small Kitchenettes<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Given that space has premium value in kitchenettes, it becomes important to be smart about storage cabinets. One may need to keep the cabinets slim but going high with tall cabinets utilises vertical space. Sliding cabinet doors also work well as they don\u2019t require clearance to swing out. Organisers and smart storage solutions further help make the most of kitchenettes. In this white kitchenette, notice how wall cabinets go up practically to the ceiling. The drawers and cupboards below are functional and house a built-in oven.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003738\/cabinets-for-small-kitchenettes.jpg\" alt=\"Kitchenette having graceful and tall cabinets\" class=\"wp-image-5194\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003738\/cabinets-for-small-kitchenettes.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003738\/cabinets-for-small-kitchenettes-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003738\/cabinets-for-small-kitchenettes-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003738\/cabinets-for-small-kitchenettes-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption>Graceful and tall cabinets in a studio kitchenette<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Open Shelves Make Kitchenettes Look Bigger<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Need storage in your kitchenette but boxy and bulky cabinets don\u2019t give you joy? Open shelving is a great kitchenette design idea. Instead of putting cabinets in, installing open shelves makes for an airy and spacious look. Floating shelves, rope shelves, hanging shelves, there are plenty of varieties of shelves that you can choose from. Remember that you must go the extra mile to keep open storage tidy and fit for display. In this small kitchenette, cabinets make up half the storage and open shelves are installed in the other half.&nbsp; The shelves are used for storing pantry items, crockery and even kitchen appliances.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003741\/open-shelves-kitchenettes.jpg\" alt=\"A kitchenette having a practical mix of closed and open storage\" class=\"wp-image-5195\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003741\/open-shelves-kitchenettes.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003741\/open-shelves-kitchenettes-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003741\/open-shelves-kitchenettes-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003741\/open-shelves-kitchenettes-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption>A practical mix of closed and open storage in a pristine kitchenette<br><div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Cool kitchen design hacks on a budget\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/17140431\/cool-kitchen-design-hacks-on-budget.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div><\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Storage Can Be Maximised with Pegs and Rails<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A cool small kitchenette design is to combine solutions such as pegs and rails with other storage such as cupboards and shelves. These take full advantage of wall space and are especially useful for awkward or large items that are otherwise difficult to store. They have the added advantage of making items accessible within arm\u2019s reach. In this lovely kitchenette, a peg rail is put up below open shelves and used to hang a variety of kitchen items. Note how colours are used as a critical design feature in this kitchenette.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003744\/small-kitchenette-design-pegs-rails.jpg\" alt=\"Small kitchenette design in which peg rail is put up below open shelves\" class=\"wp-image-5196\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003744\/small-kitchenette-design-pegs-rails.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003744\/small-kitchenette-design-pegs-rails-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003744\/small-kitchenette-design-pegs-rails-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003744\/small-kitchenette-design-pegs-rails-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption>A nifty peg rail for hanging pans, spatulas and crockery<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Tight Corners Are Turned To One\u2019s Advantage<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If your kitchenette is or is going to be in a corner, you are sure to find these kitchenette design ideas up your alley. Corners are typically awkward to utilise and become dead space which goes waste. Installing corner shelves, lazy susans, or corner cabinets help your kitchenette corner from such a fate. In this practical kitchenette, the cooktop is installed on an angled counter that is custom made to the kitchenette counter. The chimney is also similarly installed thereby fully utilising the space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003746\/corner-kitchenette-design-ideas.jpg\" alt=\"Kitchenette design that have corner shelves, lazy susans or corner cabinets\" class=\"wp-image-5197\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003746\/corner-kitchenette-design-ideas.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003746\/corner-kitchenette-design-ideas-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003746\/corner-kitchenette-design-ideas-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003746\/corner-kitchenette-design-ideas-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption>Cooktop and chimney installed in a corner kitchenette<br><div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Do you know whats trending for your kitchen countertops\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/17140915\/do-you-know-whats-trending-for-your-kitchen-countertops.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div><\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Downsizing Appliances Saves Storage Space<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A fridge has become a staple in all kitchen spaces. However, you don\u2019t always need a full-length refrigerator especially if the kitchenette is tiny. Putting in a mini-fridge allows you to have the convenience of storing the essentials without having to sacrifice too much space. Similarly, other appliances like ovens, mixers, toasters can also be downsized. This fully functional kitchenette has it all \u2013 a small fridge tucked under the countertop, an oven, a toaster and a coffee maker. What more can one want.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003749\/kitchenette-downsizing-appliances-saves-storage-space.jpg\" alt=\"A kitchenette where appliances are downsized to save storage space\" class=\"wp-image-5198\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003749\/kitchenette-downsizing-appliances-saves-storage-space.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003749\/kitchenette-downsizing-appliances-saves-storage-space-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003749\/kitchenette-downsizing-appliances-saves-storage-space-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003749\/kitchenette-downsizing-appliances-saves-storage-space-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption>All good things and appliances come in small packages!<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Stick To The Bare Necessities<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>It is easy to want it all in the kitchenettes, but we can\u2019t afford to forget that the kitchenette is not a regular sized kitchen. Restrict the appliances, dishware and crockery, and pantry items to the absolute minimum. Paring these back completely has several advantages. You will not run out of storage space and items will be easy to find and accessible when you need them. Further, the kitchenette will have a neater and tidier look and will be much easier to maintain. In the example pictured here the hob is restricted to a two burner and the serveware is kept to the minimum.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" class=\"wp-image-5199\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003752\/tiny-kitchenette.jpg\" alt=\"A tiny kitchenette will have a neater and tidier look, it is suitable for small spaces\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003752\/tiny-kitchenette.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003752\/tiny-kitchenette-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003752\/tiny-kitchenette-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003752\/tiny-kitchenette-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><\/figure>\r\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Up your kitchen organisation game with our storage ideas\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/17142233\/up-your-kitchen-organisation-game-with-our-storage-ideas.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Lights In Your Small Kitchenette<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Kitchenettes tend to be tucked away in dark corners and basements, where it is difficult to get access to natural light. Some clever lighting solutions will ensure that your kitchenette does not look dark and dingy and ensure you have enough light to cook by. In this kitchenette, lights have been installed under the cabinet making prep work a breeze. Additional lights over the hob enable you to see what is cooking.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003755\/small-kitchenette-lights.jpg\" alt=\"A kitchenette with practical lighting solutions under the cabinet\" class=\"wp-image-5200\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003755\/small-kitchenette-lights.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003755\/small-kitchenette-lights-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003755\/small-kitchenette-lights-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003755\/small-kitchenette-lights-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption>Practical lighting solutions under the cabinet and over the hob<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">All Things Bright Look Spacious<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition to clever lighting, experimenting with the light colors will also help you achieve brightness in the kitchenette. Neutral and warm colors for the cabinets and countertops, for any dishware or appliances on show, will make the kitchenette look spacious, airy, and inviting. In the example, observe how a warm yellow is set off by accents of white. Yellow cabinets are complemented by white countertops, white beading, and white backsplash. Hints of metal complete the contemporary look.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003758\/yellow-white-kitchenettes.jpg\" alt=\"A kitchenette in white and yellow color which gives you a cheerful vibe.\" class=\"wp-image-5201\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003758\/yellow-white-kitchenettes.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003758\/yellow-white-kitchenettes-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003758\/yellow-white-kitchenettes-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21003758\/yellow-white-kitchenettes-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption>A cheerful and inviting kitchen done up in cheerful yellow and white<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>While we are calling it a wrap on our list, we hope that you have enough in your arsenal to get started on your kitchenette. Keep your kitchenette light, bright, and well organized. You will barely notice not having a full-fledged kitchen and you will have the space and means for your master chef dreams to come true.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Also Read:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/5-big-stylish-ideas-for-small-kitchens\/\">5 Big Stylish Ideas for Small Kitchens<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchen-organisation-ideas\/\">10 Kitchen Organization Ideas For Your Home<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/space-saving-ideas-for-small-kitchen\/\">Space Saving Ideas For Your Small Kitchen<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Modular Kitchens At Best Prices<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p